title: `SpatialData`
text: SpatialData package contains set reader plotting functions spatial omics data stored SpatialData .zarr files, following OME-NGFF specs. SpatialData object composed five layers: images, labels, shapes, points, tables. layer may contain arbitrary number elements. Images labels represented ZarrArrays (Rarr). Points shapes represented arrow objects linked -disk .parquet file. , data represented memory. Element annotation well cross-layer summarizations (e.g., count matrices) represented SingleCellExperiment tables.

title: `SpatialData`
text: demonstration, read toy dataset available package: SpatialData object behave like list, thereby supporting flexible accession, e.g., via $ [[, using character integer indices etc. Specifically, image/label/shape/point/table() retrieve one element images/labels/shapes/points/tables() retrieve one layer image/label/shape/point/tableNames() retrieve element names Let’s demonstrate capabilities using image layer: element made two key components: data: actual array table (images/labels shapes/points, respectively) meta: list metadata retrieved OME-NGFF compliant .zattrs (stored Zattrs)
code: x <- file.path("extdata", "blobs.zarr") x <- system.file(x, package="SpatialData") (x <- readSpatialData(x)) ## class: SpatialData ## - images(2): ##   - blobs_image (3,64,64) ##   - blobs_multiscale_image (3,64,64) ## - labels(2): ##   - blobs_labels (64,64) ##   - blobs_multiscale_labels (64,64) ## - points(1): ##   - blobs_points (200) ## - shapes(3): ##   - blobs_circles (5,circle) ##   - blobs_multipolygons (2,polygon) ##   - blobs_polygons (5,polygon) ## - tables(1): ##   - table (3,10) ## coordinate systems: ## - global(8): blobs_image blobs_multiscale_image ... blobs_polygons ##   blobs_points ## - scale(1): blobs_labels ## - translation(1): blobs_labels ## - affine(1): blobs_labels ## - sequence(1): blobs_labels shapeNames(x) # there are two images shapes(x) # this is a list of them shape(x, i=1) # this is the 1st one shape(x, "blobs_polygons") # this is the 3nd one x$shapes$blobs_circles # list-like handling also works data(shape(x)) ## FileSystemDataset with 1 Parquet file ## 2 columns ## geometry: geoarrow.wkb <crs: unspecified> ## radius: int64 ##  ## See $metadata for additional Schema metadata meta(shape(x)) ## An object of class "Zattrs" ## [[1]] ## [1] "x" "y" ##  ## [[2]] ##     input.axes input.name  output.axes output.name     type ## 1 c("x", "....         xy c("x", "....      global identity ##  ## [[3]] ## [1] "ngff:shapes" ##  ## [[4]] ## [[4]]$version ## [1] "0.2"

title: `SpatialData`
text: example data, label shape polygons. labels morphological regions annotated pathologists.  also show plot transcript without cell segmentation. 2,000 cells, 3,714,642 molecules, takes long time compile. Lets crop image visualize put next original image:
code: td <- tempfile() dir.create(td) # problem in action related to file reference (URL?) scheme pa <- unzip_merfish_demo(dest=td) x <- readSpatialData(pa) i <- sample(length(p <- point(x, i=1)), 2e3) point(x, "2k") <- p[i] plotSpatialData() +     plotImage(x) +     plotPoint(x, i="2k", c="cell_type", s=0.2) +     new_scale_color() +     plotShape(x, i="anatomical") +     scale_color_manual(values=hcl.colors(6, "Spectral")) bb <- list(xmin=1500, xmax=2300, ymin=4800, ymax=5500) bb <- list(xmin=1500, xmax=2300, ymin=5500, ymax=6500) crop <- do.call(query, c(list(x=image(x)), bb)) y <- SpatialData(images=list("foo"=crop)) p <- plotSpatialData() + plotImage(x) q <- plotSpatialData() + plotImage(y) p | q
